As Indian cities grow upward to accommodate millions more, the real challenge lies beneath the surface. How do we engineer towers that are safe, efficient, and humane? How do people move through them seamlessly? And how do we design for emergencies in some of the world’s most complex urban conditions?

At the Build India Vision Summit, an initiative by FOAID, this session brings together experts unpacking what it truly takes to build tall in India — from structural resilience and construction technology to vertical mobility, fire safety, evacuation planning, and urban integration. The conversation goes beyond height and iconography to focus on performance, people, and preparedness — asking what high-rise buildings must become to support dense, fast-growing Indian cities responsibly.

